      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__iicps__api_1ga935187507d0449da043070029b9b7d25" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void XIicPs_ResetHw</definition>
        <argsstring>(UINTPTR BaseAddress)</argsstring>
        <name>XIicPs_ResetHw</name>
        <param>
          <type>UINTPTR</type>
          <declname>BaseAddress</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Performs the reset sequence to the given I2c interface by configuring the appropriate control bits in the I2c specific registers the i2cps reset sequence involves the following steps Disable all the interrupts Clear the status Clear FIFO&apos;s and disable hold bit Clear the line status Update relevant configuration registers with reset values. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Base address of the interface</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>None.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This function will not modify the slcr registers that are relevant for I2c controller </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
